provisions.content:
making any inquiry under this Ordinance, have the same powers as are vested in a civil court under
matters, namely :―
(a)        summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on
oath ;
(b)        requiring the discovery or production of any document ;
(c)        requisitioning any public record from any court or office ;
(d)        issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses ;
(e)        appointing guardians or next friends of persons who are minors or of unsound
mind ;
(f)        adding legal representatives of deceased borrowers or sureties ;
(g)        substituting the names of rightful parties ;
(h)        consolidation of cases ; and
(i)        any other matter which may be prescribed by rules made under section 6.
